<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 24px;
        color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
      }
      table {
        max-width: 600px;
        padding: 0 12px 24px 12px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
      }
      tr {
        text-align: left;
      }
      hr {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      a {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:link {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:visited {
        color: #4c6259;
      }
      a:hover {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      a:active {
        color: #ca3827;
      }
      .article-title {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .text-centered {
        text-align: center;
      }
      .pb-s {
        padding-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .pb-m {
        padding-bottom: 24px;
      }
      .pb-l {
        padding-bottom: 48px;
      }
      .pb-xl {
        padding-bottom: 56px;
      }
      .color-main {
        color: #2c3e50;
      }
      .font-s {
        font-size: 12px;
      }
    </style>
    <title>AR Weekly</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <table class="text-centered">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered">
            <img
              src="<%= @logo_url %>"
              alt="AR Weekly"
              width="100px"
              height="100px"
            />
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-centered font-s pb-xl">
            Issue #<%= @issue_number %>, <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Hello guys! This digest covers Augmented Reality related news between <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_from, "{D} {Mfull}") %> and <%= Timex.format!(@issue_date_to, "{D} {Mfull}") %>. Enjoy!
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              HoloLens 1 Put to Maintenance Mode
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            HoloLens 1 will no longer receive major operating system updates. The device will still be supported for 10 years through security updates and bugfixes. HoloLens 2 is currently available for pre-order.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://hololens.reality.news/news/microsoft-discontinuing-major-os-updates-for-hololens-1-0202380")) %>'
              >https://hololens.reality.news</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Facebook-Funded Research on Brain-Computer Interfaces (BCI) Shows First Results
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Facebook Reality Labs research and development team along with university research partners aim to solve the question of input for all-day wearable AR glasses. They see BCI as a compelling path towards a solution. To quote Facebook: "A decade from now, the ability to type directly from our brains may be accepted as a given. Not long ago, it sounded like science fiction. Now, it feels within plausible reach. And our responsibility to ensure that these technologies work for everyone begins today."
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://techcrunch.com/2019/07/30/facebook-is-exploring-brain-control-for-ar-wearables")) %>'
              >https://techcrunch.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m">
            <h1 class="article-title">
              Unity 2019.2 Brings New Features to AR Foundation
            </h1>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            AR Foundation is an SDK for the Unity game engine to build cross-platform (ARKit and ARCore) AR experiences. The 2019.2 Update includes the following features: Face-Tracking (ARKit and ARCore), 2D Image-Tracking (ARKit and ARCore), 3D Object-Tracking (ARKit), Environment Probes (ARKit), Motion Capture (ARKit), People Occlusion (ARKit), Collaborative Session (ARKit)
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-l">
          Source:
          <a href='<%= ArWeeklyWeb.Router.Helpers.page_url(ArWeeklyWeb.Endpoint, :track_issue_link, ArWeekly.EmailService.arweekly_encode(to_string(@issue_number) <> "@@" <> @subscriber_email <> "@@" <> "https://unity.com/releases/2019-2/platforms-and-editor#ar-foundation-updates")) %>'
              >https://unity.com</a
            >
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-s">
            Suggestions or comments are more than welcome! Just reply to this
            email.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-xl">
            Thanks for reading<br />
            <span class="color-main"><strong>AR</strong>&nbsp;Weekly</span>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="pb-m font-s">
            You receive this Email because you are subscribed to the AR Weekly
            Blog. Your next delivery is on <%= Timex.format!(@next_issue_date, "{D} {Mfull} {YYYY}") %>.
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-s">
            <a href="<%= @unsubscribe_url %>">Unsubscribe</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;
            |&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="<%= @privacy_url %>">Privacy Policy</a
            >&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hello@ar-weekly.blog">hello@ar-weekly.blog</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/Domeee/ar-weekly">Source Code @ GitHub</a>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <img width="1px" height="1px" src="<%= @issue_tracking_url %>" alt="">
  </body>
</html>
